TextBody:
ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000HjXUN:ref

Hey Flaviu,

Any Update on this? And if I'm understanding your response. Right Clicking and hitting Send To -> Easylock on EasyLockLauncher.exe should launch the EasyLock application every time right? It appears thats not happening if my statement is true.
Subject: Netwrix Support Ticket #425729 - EasyLock Encryption not launching

TextBody:
Hi Sean,

I have received another update on this from our engineers:

On Windows when TD1 or TD1+ right is used the root of the device cannot be accessed, ONLY the Easylock can be accessed. The Easylock app will prompt to the user(will be open) when the USB device is connected and the USB is available ONLY using Easylock.

Regarding the question: Does the EasyLockLauncher detect when EasyLock is on a USB and then launches it or does it use another method? Like having the EPPNotifier do the detection and call the EasyLockLauncher to launch it.

Answer: The epp agent will detect the Easylock if it is on USB device, NOT the EasyLockLauncher.

Please let me know if this helps.

Best Regards,

On Windows when TD1 or TD1+ right is used the root of the device cannot be accessed, ONLY the Easylock can be accessed. The Easylock app will prompt to the user(will be open) when the USB device is connected and the USB is available ONLY using Easylock.

Regarding the question: Does the EasyLockLauncher detect when EasyLock is on a USB and then launches it or does it use another method? Like having the EPPNotifier do the detection and call the EasyLockLauncher to launch it.

Answer: The epp agent will detect the Easylock if it is on USB device, NOT the EasyLockLauncher.
